  "text": "The ratio of read depth per window (W RdRatio ) is then corrected for GC content according to published methodology [CITATION_1] . The resulting GC-corrected W RdRatio data are segmented using circular binary segmentation, resulting in genomic segments and associated segmental LogRatios summarized from the GC-corrected W RdRatio of all 100-bp windows within each segment. The resulting distribution of genome-wide segmental LogRatios in the normal-normal comparisons is adjusted to be distributed around zero by subtracting the mode of the distribution from each of the segmental LogRatios.",
